## ðŸ“ˆ 5. Detailed Statistical Analysis

### 5.1. Dimensional Correlation Analysis: The Structure of Emotional Climates

The Pearson correlation matrix reveals the underlying relationships between the six ECF dimensions. These correlations are not just statistical artifacts; they reflect coherent rhetorical strategies where certain emotional appeals are mutually reinforcing or exclusive.

#### Key Dimensional Relationships
| Dimension 1 | Dimension 2 | Correlation (r) | Strength | Interpretation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| ðŸ˜  **Enmity** | ðŸ˜Š **Compersion** | **-0.91** | **Very Strong Negative** | Rhetorically opposed; attacking an opponent precludes celebrating them. |
| âœ¨ **Hope** | ðŸ¤ **Amity** | **+0.87** | **Very Strong Positive** | Synergistic; calls for unity are used to build a hopeful future. |
| ðŸ¤ **Amity** | ðŸ˜Š **Compersion** | **+0.73** | Strong Positive | Cooperative language aligns with celebrating others' merits. |
| ðŸ˜¨ **Fear** | ðŸ˜’ **Envy** | **+0.57** | Moderate Positive | Threats are often linked to the malign actions of a resented group. |

